<http://example.org/design-grammar#ParamState> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Definition state — a named set of Number/Integer/Boolean parameters captured from Grasshopper sliders and toggles. Represents the current parametric configuration. When ParamState changes, dependent IdRefs regenerate. ID prefix: DS_."@en .
<http://example.org/design-grammar/comp#hasProcedure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Connects an Algorithm to its constituent Procedures. An Algorithm contains multiple Procedures."@en .
