<http://example.org/design-grammar/meta#Variable> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A SWRL variable (e.g. ?b, ?h). Key property: name (prefixed with '?'). Every Variable individual is necessarily an ObjectVariable, PropertyVariable, OR BuiltinVariable (owl:disjointUnionOf below — VTYP-01 priority chain). MERGE key includes project to prevent cross-project collision (SCHM-02). STORAGE NOTE: In the Neo4j layer, variable kind is inferred at read time by VariableTypeInferrer.Infer() — not stored on the Var node. The OWL ontology uses rdf:type plus disjointUnionOf to discriminate; no separate kind property exists (v4.1)."@en .
